Since we are concerned with radial directions we have Î¸ and Î¦ symmetry. This means that no temperature gradient in Î¦ and Î¸ direction. Diving both the sides of above equation by r2 : âˆ‚T / âˆ‚r = - (q / 3k) r + c / r2 Integrating again we get: T (r) = - (q / 6k) r2 - c / r + d where d is another constant of integration. The following boundar conditions can be used to obtain the constants c and d : at r = 0 ; T has a finite value.
